1.0 Introduction

2.0 Installing nsd

2.1 Building nsd

First, unpack the sources into a working directory somewhere for example with:

tar -xzvf nsd.tar.gz

This will unpack the source into a directory ./nsd

Then cd nsd

Type make

XXX to be written

3.0 Configuring nsd

4.0 Running nsd

Compile a zone with

zonec -z zone-name zone-file

This will create a default database file ./nsd.db

Then run nsd with nsd ./nsd.db

By default for testing port 4096


